originalText.text: Parking attendant extremely rude.  He stares at you and demands you treat him nicely when he is rude and yelling at his customers.  Unacceptable service. Do not park here

originalText.text: This place has terrible customer service. We used spot hero to setup a reservation as we always do for these places and they guy asked me what time I’m staying till. I told him we have the spot hero app and I’m trying to show him the scan for proof. He said very rudely to me “I didn’t ask you about that what time” I told him 1am. Then he tried to walk off but we called him out about his attitude and he tried to act like he was not rude to us an brushed us off. When we came back and the gate was down, we rang the buzzer and another angry person who obviously hates his job gave us attitude acting like we buzzed him 5 times when we just got there. These attendants are disrespectful and disgusting and should be fired. DO NOT USE THIS PLACE NEVER AGAIN

originalText.text: Left our car here overnight and the attendants apparently decided to enjoy it. Smoked in it (ashes all over the seats, wreaks of smoke) and ate in it (crumbs all over the floor and cup holders). Unbelievable.

originalText.text: This is a terrible parking lot.  Saturday night we pre-booked for a show at Madison Square Garden.  Seeing that this place was only a few mins from Madison square garden we arrived 15 minutes early to the garage.  I waited almost 1 hour to have my car parked.  It was hard to get upset when it was one kid that was left all alone to park all the cars that had a prepaid.  There are many garages in the area , cheaper too.  Don’t waste your money or your time here .    This garage is poorly managed.    Don’t ever book here & yes I missed most of my show .  Not worth it and nothing to comp the customers .
